<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/679:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-13T17:00:00-05:00">December 13, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>143. Your 118, December 10, 6 p.m., last two paragraphs. I appreciate Mr.
                            Motta’s desire to be helpful and would be gratified if he would make
                            public a communiqué.<note n="8" xml:id="d383fn8">Publication was set for
                                December 16, 1929 (861.77 Chinese Eastern/680).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>